    "body": "\n> *Itâ€™s crazy â€¦ I know Iâ€™ve been through some rough times, but i had no idea how much those experiences had an impact on my day to day life!*\n\n> *Iâ€™m finally sleeping through the WHOLE night, my grades are up, people keep telling me how much pleasant it is to be around me, and I feel like I can THINK again. Thank you!â€* - **Sol**\n\nA very religious student, came to see me at her 20â€™s. First time she was raped was at age 16. Not once, not twice, but a few times a week (sometimes a day!) for almost a year, by an authority figure in her community, which she did not want to disclose or press charges against.\n \nShe didnâ€™t have a specific â€œthingâ€ she wanted to do or work on. She just said her life is a mess, and her mind is cluttered all the time.\n \nFirst thing weâ€™ve done was to [clean the trauma](/tools/trauma-relief/) and re-encode all those experiences in a less tense way.\n \nThen we connected the experience to feelings of hope, possibility, and self confidence (*â€œnow that uâ€™ve got over that, thereâ€™s no telling what you could do!â€œ*).\n \nLastly, we tied it up with [beliefs](/tools/internal-dialog-scrambler/) and behaviors of self worth, so people would stop walking all over her, which apparently happened constantly in her life.\n \nIn total weâ€™ve done 5-6 sessions, which resulted in â€¦\n \nGrades average -> up by 20 points\nWeight -> down by 6 Kgs\n \nBut most importantly, as she says â€¦\n \nSol: *â€œItâ€™s crazy â€¦ I know Iâ€™ve been through some rough times, but i had no idea how much those experiences had an impact on my day to day life!*\n \n*Iâ€™m finally sleeping through the WHOLE night, my grades are up, people keep telling me how much pleasant it is to be around me, and I feel like I can THINK again. Thank you!â€*\n",
    "ps": "\nIf you know anyone who's still controlled by her past, [contact me](/lets-talk/) and we'll get her some relief as soon as possible.\n",
