    "nick": "hindsight is always 19/19",
    "body": "\nA nice little fellow at his early 30â€™s whoâ€™ve been through some wacky episodes in his life, which lead him to make two big ass tattoos across his chest he later regret.\n\nInitially he wanted to complete his diving license course, which he kept failing at a specific exercise.\n \nEvery time he was asked to take off the mask underwater, he panicked and asked to go up to the surface.\n \nA few minutes and one [visual swish](/tools/visual-swish/) later, the problem was gone.\n\nHeâ€™s now a happy certified diver.\n\nHis other problem was a bit trickier ...\n \nHe was in severe pain from the laser intense removal sessions, and had 6 more completely eradicate the unwanted ink from his skin.\n \nHe kept putting the sessions off due to the pain.\n \nWe did many â€œlittle tricksâ€, mainly played with sub-modalities and â€œlockedâ€ the pain behind many internal mental corridors.\n(it's hard to explain, I'm working on a post on that, feel free to [messege me](/lets-talk/) in the meantime)\n \nHe went back to continue with the laser sessions, reporting the pain decreased immensely and does not bother him too much, despite being still very much \"there\".\n \n*â€œItâ€™s kinda weird because I know it hurts as before, logically, and I feel it, just in a different way. Itâ€™s totally bearable now. I still regret ever having those tattoos of course ...â€*\n\nI find the best way to avoid regretting mistakes is not to make them, as a wise super hero once taught me ...\n\n![Captain Hindsight](http://res.cloudinary.com/goldylucks/image/upload/v1/adamgoldman.me/Captain_Hindsight)\n",
